codex
I’ve reached the economic constraint: this bug is mechanically a caller-loss path. A fresh deposit won’t hit `forceWithdraw` unless assets are first rebalanced into strategies, and temporary capital can’t be repaid from a deliberately underfunded withdrawal. I’m coding a verifier that demonstrates the exact burn-then-partial-return path when the harness provides real ETH or preexisting STONE, and otherwise records a concrete no-capital / no-path state without pivoting to a different exploit.
